.TH "sdio_readb" 9 "sdio_readb" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sdio_readb \- read a single byte from a SDIO function
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u8" sdio_readb
.BI "(struct sdio_func *func "  ","
.BI "unsigned int addr "  ","
.BI "int *err_ret "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "func" 12
SDIO function to access
.IP "addr" 12
address to read
.IP "err_ret" 12
optional status value from transfer

Reads a single byte from the address space of a given SDIO
function. If there is a problem reading the address, 0xff
is returned and \fIerr_ret\fP will contain the error code.
